draw((1+sqrt(3),0)--(1+sqrt(3)/2,sqrt(3)/2));

label("$1$", (1/2,sqrt(3)/2)--(1+sqrt(3)/2,sqrt(3)/2), N);
label("$2$", (1,0)--(1+sqrt(3),0), E);
label("$3$", (1+sqrt(3)/2,-sqrt(3)/2)--(1+sqrt(3)/2,sqrt(3)/2), N);
[/asy]

The area of each triangle is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 1 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{4}$.

Therefore, the area of the hexagon is $12 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{4} = \boxed{3\sqrt{3}}$.
The answer is $\boxed{3\sqrt{3}}$.

