 [asy]
pair A,B,C,D;

A = (0,0);
B = (1,0);
D = rotate(105)*(0.6,0);
C = D+B-A;
draw(A--B--C--D--A);
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$62^\circ$",(A+B)/2,S);
label("$75^\circ$",(B+D)/2,W);
draw(B--D,dashed);
[/asy]

Since $\overline{AB}\parallel\overline{CD}$, we have $\angle B + \angle C = 180^\circ$.  Since $\angle B = 180^\circ - \angle A = 118^\circ$, we have $\angle C = 62^\circ$.

Since $\overline{AD}\parallel\overline{BC}$, we have $\angle C +\angle CDA = 180^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle CDA = 180^\circ - \angle C = \boxed{118^\circ}$.

