\[\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -3 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} + t \left( \begin{pmatrix} -11 \\ 1 \\ 28 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -3 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} \right) = \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -3 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} + t \begin{pmatrix} -16 \\ 4 \\ 32 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 - 16t \\ -3 + 4t \\ -4 + 32t \end{pmatrix}.\]Let $\mathbf{p} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -3 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\mathbf{d} = \begin{pmatrix} -16 \\ 4 \\ 32 \end{pmatrix}.$  Then $\mathbf{v} = \mathbf{p} + \mathbf{d} t.$

