\[\|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{a}\| = \|\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a}\| \cdot \|t\| = \|\mathbf{d}\| \cdot |t| = \|\mathbf{d} t\| = \|\mathbf{v} - (\mathbf{p} + \mathbf{d} t)\| = \|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{v}\| = 0.\]This is consistent with the given condition that the distance between $\mathbf{v}$ and $\mathbf{a}$ is $t.$

