Note that line $AB$ is the perpendicular bisector of $\overline{PQ},$ so
\[\frac{P + Q}{2} = \frac{A + B}{2}.\]Hence,
\[Q = \frac{A + B}{2} + \frac{A - B}{2} \cdot \frac{P - \frac{A + B}{2}}{A - B}.\]We can compute that $\frac{A + B}{2} = \begin{pmatrix} 9/2 \\ 3/2 \end{pmatrix},$ and $A - B = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix},$ and $P - \frac{A + B}{2} = \begin{pmatrix} -5/2 \\ 3/2 \end{pmatrix}.$  Therefore,
\[Q = \begin{pmatrix} 9/2 \\ 3/2 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \frac{\begin{pmatrix} -5/2 \\ 3/2 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -5/2 \\ 3/2 \end{pmatrix}} = \begin{pmatrix} -1/2 \\ 7/2 \end{pmatrix}.\]The line connecting $P$ and $Q$ is then given by $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} + t \left( \begin{pmatrix} -1/2 \\ 7/2 \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \right)}.$

