We are asked to find the rectangular coordinates of the point with spherical coordinates $(\rho, \theta, 3 \phi)$. We can substitute these values into the equations above to find the rectangular coordinates:
\begin{align*}
x &= \rho \sin (3 \phi) \cos \theta = 2 \sin (3 \phi) \cos \theta, \\
y &= \rho \sin (3 \phi) \sin \theta = 2 \sin (3 \phi) \sin \theta, \\
z &= \rho \cos (3 \phi) = 2 \cos (3 \phi).
\end{align*}
We can use the trigonometric identity $\sin 3\phi = 3\sin \phi - 4\sin^3 \phi$ and $\cos 3\phi = 4\cos^3 \phi - 3\cos \phi$ to simplify the expressions for $x$, $y$, and $z$:
\begin{align*}
x &= 2(3\sin \phi - 4\sin^3 \phi) \cos \theta = 6\sin \phi \cos \theta - 8\sin^3 \phi \cos \theta, \\
y &= 2(3\sin \phi - 4\sin^3 \phi) \sin \theta = 6\sin \phi \sin \theta - 8\sin^3 \phi \sin \theta, \\
z &= 2(4\cos^3 \phi - 3\cos \phi) = 8\cos^3 \phi - 6\cos \phi.
\end{align*}
We can substitute the expressions for $\sin \phi$ and $\cos \phi$ from the original equations into these expressions:
\begin{align*}
x &= 6\left(\frac{2}{\rho}\right) \cos \theta - 8\left(\frac{2}{\rho}\right)^3 \cos \theta = \frac{24}{\rho} \cos \theta - \frac{32}{\rho^3} \cos \theta, \\
y &= 6\left(\frac{-1}{\rho}\right) \sin \theta - 8\left(\frac{-1}{\rho}\right)^3 \sin \theta = \frac{-6}{\rho} \sin \theta + \frac{8}{\rho^3} \sin \theta, \\
z &= 8\left(\frac{-2}{\rho}\right)^3 - 6\left(\frac{-2}{\rho}\right) = \frac{-32}{\rho^3} + \frac{12}{\rho}.
\end{align*}
Finally, we can substitute the values of $\rho = 2$ into these expressions to find the rectangular coordinates of the point with spherical coordinates $(\rho, \theta, 3 \phi)$:
\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{24}{2} \cos \theta - \frac{32}{2^3} \cos \theta = 12 \cos \theta - 4 \cos \theta = 8 \cos \theta, \\
y &= \frac{-6}{2} \sin \theta + \frac{8}{2^3} \sin \theta = -3 \sin \theta + \frac{1}{2} \sin \theta = -\frac{5}{2} \sin \theta, \\
z &= \frac{-32}{2^3} + \frac{12}{2} = -4 + 6 = 2.
\end{align*}
Therefore, the rectangular coordinates of the point with spherical coordinates $(\rho, \theta, 3 \phi)$ are $(8 \cos \theta, -\frac{5}{2} \sin \theta, 2)$.
